The answer is to create a balanced binary search tree as follows.  The mid point is the root.  Recursively generate the tree on the left and the right.  Like this untested code.

    def make_tree (elements, left=None, right=None):
        if left is None:
            left = 0
        if right is None:
            right = len(elements) - 1

        middle = (left + right) // 2
        answer = Node(middle)
        if left &lt; middle:
            answer.left = make_tree(elements, left, middle - 1)
        if middle &lt; right:
            answer.right = make_tree(elements, middle + 1, right)
        return answer

This function will be called once with each element as `middle`, and does `O(1)` work each time.  So it is `O(n)`.

